---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — TrackMarc Motorsport Photography"
  description="Marc is an independent motorsport photographer covering Formula, WEC, WRC, and GT racing across Europe."
>
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-photo-wrap">
      <div class="about-photo">
        <div class="photo-placeholder" style="position:absolute; inset:0;">
          <div class="photo-placeholder-icon">📷</div>
          <div class="photo-placeholder-text">Your portrait</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="about-photo-caption">At the pit entry, Le Mans 2024</p>

      <div class="accreditation-box" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <h4>Media Credentials Held</h4>
        <p>FIA Formula 2 &bull; FIA WRC &bull; WEC / ELMS &bull; GT World Challenge &bull; National Championships (IRL, UK)</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-text">
      <p class="about-role">Independent Motorsport Photographer</p>
      <h1>Marc<br /><em>Ronan</em></h1>

      <p>
        I started following motorsport with a camera in 2019, initially at club-level events in
        Ireland before working my way up through national championships and eventually to
        FIA-sanctioned series across Europe.
      </p>
      <p>
        What drew me to motorsport photography isn't the machinery — it's the human story running
        parallel to it. The sleep-deprived engineer checking tyre temperatures at 3am at Le Mans.
        The rookie driver composing themselves on the grid. The mechanic's quiet pride after a
        flawless pitstop.
      </p>
      <p>
        I shoot to tell those stories. The car is the setting; the people are the subject.
      </p>

      <h3 class="about-section-title">Approach</h3>
      <p>
        I work light and fast — a two-body kit that lets me move between the pit lane, grandstands,
        and permitted trackside positions without a support team. My background in documentary
        photography means I'm comfortable working long events and waiting for the decisive moment
        rather than spraying and praying.
      </p>
      <p>
        Turnaround is typically same-day for editorial use, with fully edited selects delivered
        within 24 hours of an event.
      </p>

      <h3 class="about-section-title">Equipment</h3>
      <ul class="gear-list">
        <li>Sony A9 III (primary body)</li>
        <li>Sony A7 IV (secondary / video)</li>
        <li>Sony 400mm f/2.8 GM OSS</li>
        <li>Sony 70-200mm f/2.8 GM OSS II</li>
        <li>Sony 24-70mm f/2.8 GM II</li>
        <li>Sony 16-35mm f/2.8 GM II</li>
        <li>Peak Design harness system</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="about-section-title">Selected Coverage (2022–2024)</h3>
      <ul class="gear-list">
        <li>Le Mans 24 Hours — 2022, 2023, 2024</li>
        <li>FIA WRC Rally Catalunya 2024</li>
        <li>FIA Formula 2 — Silverstone, Monza 2024</li>
        <li>GT World Challenge Europe — Spa, Paul Ricard 2024</li>
        <li>ELMS — Portimão, Imola 2023–24</li>
        <li>Porsche Carrera Cup GB — multiple rounds 2023–24</li>
        <li>Radical European Masters — Spa 2023</li>
        <li>Mondello Park Nationals — 2022–2024</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="accreditation-box" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <h4>Seeking Accreditation</h4>
        <p>
          I'm actively building my credentials portfolio with the goal of earning FIA Formula 1 and
          full FIA World Championship accreditation. If you're a press officer, series coordinator,
          or team media manager and see potential in my work, I'd love to hear from you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
